AGI - Always longer waiting lists, hospitals without doctors in the afternoon, increasingly rich private health. These are the consequences that Maurizio Viecca, chief of the Sacco hospital, sees in the novelty of the obligation to recover the hours worked more introduced by the new contract of doctors, in force for a few weeks. "I make an example: if a doctor works several hours a month then he has to stay at home at rest - he explains to AGI -. Since every doctor accumulates on average about 20 hours a month, maybe because he works on the weekend or does the guard shifts, which are mandatory, it means that, when everyone gets back extra hours, we will close the hospitals at two o'clock in the afternoon. The public would have disastrous consequences, with the waiting lists that would be far more crazy.» The private will become even richer because the patients, finding the clinics closed on afternoon hours, would turn elsewhere. Moreover, Italy is the only European country where there is no problem of ensuring adequate performance even in the afternoon ".
&nbsp;
According to the Milan cardiologist, there are two possible solutions to overcome this problem: "Or you increase your medical staff or pay for the overtime that is now paid only in special cases. The first solution is the most difficult, considering the shortage of doctors as well as nurses, and also the most honest. Italian doctors are in the penultimate place in the European salaries ranking, worse than we are only Greece."
&nbsp;
What happened first in case of extra work?. "There was no precise rule, everyone did what he wanted," says Viecca. Now rightly, health administrations will be obliged to comply with the new rule. We think a patient should die for a hypothetical medical fault. The Prosecutor would say that this would happen because the doctor did not rest enough if he did not comply with the rule of rest. The damage of this novelty will not be seen immediately but as they will accumulate the rest»". The primary suggests another possibility to strengthen health: "It would be necessary to give pensioners the opportunity to stop at the hospital. What? Giving him the liquidation immediately and paying him a normal salary, obviously without the contributions "&nbsp;

